      "content": "but how can you say i'm not being replaced when the 'me' on the internet is actually the one communicating with everyone? my friends are all talking to the version of me that exists in the cloud. if that version is more active and more 'me' than i am in real life, then for all intents and purposes, isn't that who i am now? it feels like the digital ghost has already taken over my life and i'm just stuck on the outside watching it happen.",
